      <h2>Beko fact-accuracy — what this brand is and isn't</h2>
      <p>
        Beko carries some brand-identity confusion that's worth clearing up before any service call.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Beko ≠ commercial brand in US residential scope.</b> Despite Arçelik's international
        commercial-foodservice operations and a narrow US foodservice product called Beko Pro, the
        Beko-branded consumer dishwashers you buy at Home Depot, Lowe's, Best Buy, Costco, AJ
        Madison, and specialty appliance showrooms are residential. 99% of the US Beko installed
        base is consumer residential.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Beko ≠ Whirlpool or Samsung.</b> Beko is frequently misattributed to larger US brands.
        Arçelik is an independent Turkish conglomerate (founded 1955, Istanbul), entirely separate
        from Whirlpool Corporation, Samsung Electronics, or other US-familiar appliance parents.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Blomberg is Beko's sibling, not a separate competitor.</b> If your household has both a
        Beko and a Blomberg appliance, they're both Arçelik brands with shared platform DNA on many
        service items. Service path is the same for both.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Grundig is also Arçelik.</b> Grundig audio/video + some appliance products share the same
        parent. Less common in LA residential dishwasher market but occasionally encountered.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

